<title>UK: British Telecom to set $1.0 bln 5-yr bond.</title>
<headline>British Telecom to set $1.0 bln 5-yr bond.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>British Telecommunications Plc will launch a $1.0 billion five-year Eurobond in the near future, SBC Warburg said as joint lead manager.</p>
<p>Merrill Lynch will be the other joint lead manager.  </p>
<p>BT lost its AAA Moody's rating in mid-February and is now Aa1. BT's AAA long-term debt rating from Standard &amp; Poor is under review for a possible downgrade.</p>
<p>--London newsroom +44 171 542 8863</p>
